                                                    <edge COLOR="#2fd8a7" WIDTH="4"/>
                                                    <richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html><head/><body>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold">Jacob / Israel</span></p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold">N</span><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">ame: יַעֲקֹב (Ya'aqov) — from עקב ('aqev), "heel." </span></p>
                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Named because he was born grasping his </span></p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">twin Esau's heel (Genesis 25:26). </span></p>
                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">The root also carries "to follow at the heel," </span></p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">"to supplant," "to deceive."</span></p>
                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Renamed: יִשְׂרָאֵל (Yisra'el) — </span></p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">given after wrestling the unnamed figure at </span></p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">the Jabbok ford (Genesis 32:28). </span></p>
                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">The text glosses it as "you have striven (sarita) </span></p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">with God and with men, and have prevailed." </span></p>
                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Often translated "He Who Wrestles With God"</span></p>
                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Walks away with a permanent limp.</span></p>
                                                    </body></html></richcontent>
