                                                                    <edge COLOR="#79997f" WIDTH="4"/>
                                                                    <richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html><head/><body>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold">Nahshon</span></p>
                                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Nahshon (נַחְשׁוֹן) —</span></p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> from נָחָשׁ (nachash, "serpent") </span></p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">with an intensive suffix.</span></p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> "The great serpent" or "the diviner."</span></p>
                                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> This is a loaded name</span></p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">nachash is the Eden serpent word, </span></p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">but also carries connotations of bronze/copper</span></p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> (נְחֹשֶׁת, nechoshet) and divination/observation. </span></p>
                                                                      <p>&#160;</p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Nahshon is prince of Judah in the wilderness </span></p>
                                                                      <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">(Numbers 2:3)</span></p>
                                                                    </body></html></richcontent>
