                                                      <node ID="ID_330618568" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#141414" COLOR="#ffffff" POSITION="left" HGAP_QUANTITY="293 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="293 px" MIN_WIDTH="723" MAX_WIDTH="723">
                                                        <font NAME="LiberationSans" SIZE="22" BOLD="true"/>
                                                        <edge COLOR="#8c2189" WIDTH="4"/>
                                                        <richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html><head/><body>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold">Ben-Oni</span><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff"> </span><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold">Benjamin</span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff">"son of the right hand"</span></p>
                                                          <p>&#160;</p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold">Ben-Oni</span><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff"> (בֶּן־אוֹנִי) </span></p>
                                                          <p>&#160;</p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Rachel's name for her second son, </span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">spoken as she dies in childbirth (Genesis 35:18). </span></p>
                                                          <p>&#160;</p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">The root און (on) carries simultaneous meanings </span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">that cannot be separated without losing the name's force: </span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">sexual/procreative potency, vital strength, sorrow, and trouble. </span></p>
                                                          <p>&#160;</p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Rachel's naming collapses all of these into a single</span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> utterance — this child is the son of her husband's</span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> virility, the son of her own life-force spent, and the son</span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> of her death-agony, all at once. The act that created him is</span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> the act that destroyed her. </span></p>
                                                          <p>&#160;</p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Jacob immediately renames him </span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic">Benjamin ("son of the right hand"),</span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> replacing the raw embodied truth with</span></p>
                                                          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 22pt; color: #ffffff; font-style: italic"> something politically auspicious</span></p>
                                                        </body></html></richcontent>
                                                      </node>
                                                    </node>
