      <node ID="ID_351887472" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#141414" COLOR="#ffffff" POSITION="left" HGAP_QUANTITY="336 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="-1375 px" MIN_WIDTH="1055" MAX_WIDTH="1055">
        <font NAME="LiberationSans" SIZE="43" BOLD="true"/>
        <edge COLOR="#cecf4d" WIDTH="4"/>
        <richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html><head/><body>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 43pt; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold">The tree of knowing good and evil</span></p>
          <p>&#160;</p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">The → הַ (ha) — definite article. Specific, singular, set apart.</span></p>
          <p>&#160;</p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">tree → עֵץ (ets) — tree, wood, timber. </span></p>
          <p>&#160;</p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">Possibly rooted in עצה/עצם suggesting firmness, substance, structure. The thing that holds and transmits.</span></p>
          <p>&#160;</p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">of the knowing → דַּעַת (da'at) — verbal noun from ידע (yada). Not information but transformative participatory contact.</span></p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff"> The verb for sexual union, covenant intimacy, craft mastery. </span></p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">You don't yada something and remain what you were.</span></p>
          <p>&#160;</p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">of good → טוֹב (tov) — functional, ripe, beautiful, beneficial, </span></p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">fit-for-purpose, complete. </span></p>
          <p>&#160;</p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">and → וָ (va) — conjunction, but in paired constructions can signal spectrum, tension, or totality. The hinge between poles.</span></p>
          <p>&#160;</p>
          <p><span style="font-family: LiberationSans; font-size: 29pt; color: #ffffff">evil → רָע (ra) — harmful, broken, spoiled, ugly, calamitous, dysfunctional. Not abstract metaphysical evil but the experienced quality of things that damage and diminish. Bad fruit, bad road, bad outcome.</span></p>
        </body></html></richcontent>
      </node>
    </node>
